## Code conventions
- ALL components are functional components with TypeScript
- NEVER use class-based components
- NEVER use Redux or Context API for server state — use TanStack Query
- NEVER use useState for server data — use useQuery/useMutation
- NEVER write inline styles — always use Tailwind utility classes
- NEVER use fetch() directly — always use the Axios instance from src/lib/axios.ts
- Use named exports for components, default exports for pages
- Co-locate types with their component: ProductCard.tsx + ProductCard.types.ts
- Query keys: arrays — ['products', id], ['cart', userId], ['benchmark']

## Folder structure
src/
  pages/          ← route-level pages (Login, Products, Cart, Benchmark, Dashboard)
  components/     ← reusable UI components
    auth/         ← LoginForm, OAuthButtons, ProtectedRoute
    products/     ← ProductCard, ProductTable, ProductForm
    cart/         ← CartDrawer, CartItem
    benchmark/    ← BenchmarkChart, BenchmarkResult
    layout/       ← Navbar, Sidebar, PageWrapper
  lib/
    axios.ts      ← Axios instance with interceptors
    queryClient.ts ← TanStack Query client config
  store/
    authStore.ts  ← Zustand: { user, isAuthenticated, login, logout }
    cartStore.ts  ← Zustand: { items, addItem, removeItem }
  hooks/
    useProducts.ts
    useCart.ts
    useBenchmark.ts
  types/
    api.types.ts  ← TypeScript interfaces matching Spring DTOs

## Design system
- Font: 'Bricolage Grotesque' (display) + 'DM Sans' (body)
- Color palette: dark navy (#0F172A) + electric blue (#3B82F6) + warm amber (#F59E0B)
- Dark mode first — bg-slate-950 base, text-slate-100
- Tailwind dark: prefix used throughout
- No rounded-full on rectangular elements — use rounded-lg max
- shadcn/ui components as base — extend, do not override

## Auth flow
- On app load: call GET /api/auth/me to restore session from httpOnly cookie
- If 401: user is not logged in, redirect to /login
- Google OAuth: window.location.href = '/oauth2/authorization/google'
  Spring Security handles the entire OAuth2 flow and sets the cookie
  After success: Spring redirects to /?auth=success, React reads this and restores state
- ProtectedRoute: wraps all authenticated routes, checks authStore.isAuthenticated

## Do NOT
- Do not store JWT in localStorage (XSS risk) — it lives in httpOnly cookie only
- Do not call /oauth2/* via Axios — it's a full page redirect
- Do not create API endpoints that don't exist in the backend list above
- Do not use any CSS framework other than Tailwind
- Do not use moment.js — use date-fns